{{Infobox forest | name = April Salome Forest Management Area | native_name = April — Salumei Rainforest | native_lang = | native_name2 = | native_lang2 = | photo = | photo_caption = | photo_width = | map = Papua New Guinea | relief = yes | map_caption = | map_width = | coordinates = {{Coord|4|38|15.3|S|142|46|37.0|E|region:PG_type:mountain_scale:300000|display=inline,title}} | county = | region = | country = {{PNG}} | elevation = | area = 521,500 hectares | max_area = | date_max_area = | status = | established = | visitation = | visitation_year = | events = | authority = | website = | ecosystem = [[Tropical rainforest]] | classification_WWF = | classification_EPA = | classification_CEC = | disturbance = | forest_cover = | species = | indicator_plants = | lesser_flora = | fauna = }} '''April Salome Forest Management Area''' also known as '''April Salumei Rainforest''' <ref name="filer" /><ref name="stand">[https://standfortrees.org/en/protect-a-forest/april-salumei-rainforest-conservation-project April Salumei Rainforest Conservation project]</ref> is a [[forest management]] area in April — Salumei [[tropical forest]] covering about 521,500 hectares<ref name="filer" /> in [[Ambunti-Dreikikir District]] of [[East Sepik Province]], of [[Papua New Guinea]].<ref>[https://www.cairnscharts.com.au/collections/png-topographic-maps/products/ga7489 Map GA 7489] Publisher: Geoscience Australia (Australian Government) </ref> Forest resides in the basins of two rivers: April<ref name="april">[https://geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-3024020&fid=4865&c=papua_new_guinea April River: Papua New Guinea] National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency, Bethesda, MD, USA </ref> and Salumei.<ref name="salumei">[https://geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-3044117&fid=4856&c=papua_new_guinea Salumei River: Papua New Guinea] National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency, Bethesda, MD, USA </ref> Town [[Ambunti]] serves as a gateway to the April Salome Forest Management Area.<ref>[https://placesmap.net/PG/April-Salome-Forest-Management-Area-2747005/ April Salome Forest Management Area] PlacesMap.net</ref> == Population == It is estimated that about 20,000 people are living in this area<ref>[http://natashaloder.blogspot.com/2009/06/april-salome.html April Salome]</ref> in 164 forest-dependent communities.<ref name="stand" /> Populated places include Nakek<ref>[https://geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-3040024&fid=4848&c=papua_new_guinea Nakek: Papua New Guinea] National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency, Bethesda, MD, USA</ref> and Uwu<ref>[https://geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-3048333&fid=4858&c=papua_new_guinea Uwu: Papua New Guinea] National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency, Bethesda, MD, USA</ref>. == Geography == April Salome Forest Management Area is located in the [[Sepik]] river basin. Sepik tributary, the April river is the major river in the area.<ref name="april" />
