'''Litvinenko Justice Foundation''' is a non-profit organization established to demand justice for [[Alexander Litvinenko]] who [[Alexander Litvinenko poisoning|was allegedly poisoned]] in [[London]], [[United Kingdom]] on November 1, 2006.
According to organizers, they will do “everything possible to make sure that suspects will stand trial in the U.K. and will not be shielded from justice by the Russian state.” <ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2007/04/03/world/europe/03cnd-spy.html Foundation Set Up to Seek Justice for Ex-K.G.B. Spy], by Alan Cowell, [[New York Times]], April 3, 2007</ref>
The Litvinenko Justice Foundation was founded by [[Alexander Litvinenko]]'s widow, Marina, and his two friends, [[Boris Berezovsky (businessman)|Boris Berezovsky]] and [[Alexander Goldfarb (microbiologist)|Alex Goldfarb]]. They were joined by a prominent human rights lawyer [[Louise Christian]].
The Foundation was registered in London, United Kingdom on 2 March 2007. Initial funding was provided by Boris Berezovsky [http://en.rian.ru/world/20070405/63175922.html].
After Marina Litvinenko was granted an [[inquest]] into the death of her husband in October 2011, the Foundation launched a public fundraising campaign to help her offset her legal costs. <ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-15334401 Litvinenko's widow appeals for inquest funding.][[BBC News]], 17 October 2011</ref>
